  "market_context": "DXY on the daily chart in June 2023, with a daily fair value gap resting around 101.900–102.100 below price acting as a downside point of interest after a sustained move lower from the 104.000 area.",
  "key_observation": "After sweeping a swing low into the daily FVG point of interest, the down-close candle that completed the sweep becomes a bullish order block; once price closes above its high, the order block supports price higher toward previous highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the daily fair value gap resting below price around 101.900–102.100 as the downside point of interest.",
    "Note a swing low forming above the FVG, leaving sellside liquidity resting just above the point of interest.",
    "Observe price filling the daily FVG and the next day sweeping the swing low directly into the point of interest.",
    "Mark the down-close candle that performed the sweep into the POI as the order block of interest.",
    "Wait for price to close above the high of that down-close order block to confirm the reversal.",
    "Anticipate a retrace into the opening price of the order block, noting a fair value gap also forms in the move higher.",
    "Confirm price reaches into the OB but closes outside its opening price, validating it as support.",
    "Project continuation higher the following day toward the previous swing high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price closed above the order block, respected its opening price on the retrace, and continued higher toward the previous high — illustrative bullish reversal example.",
  "lessons": "When price sweeps a swing low into a higher-timeframe FVG point of interest, the down-close candle that delivered the sweep becomes a high-probability bullish order block; a close above it signals the reversal and its opening price offers an entry.",
